    "response": "To compute the **sample standard deviation** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{-11, 9, 5, 15, -10, -15, 12, -25, -22\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the mean (average) of the data set\n\n$$\n\\text{Mean} = \\frac{-11 + 9 + 5 + 15 - 10 - 15 + 12 - 25 - 22}{9}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{-11 + 9 = -2; -2 + 5 = 3; 3 + 15 = 18; 18 - 10 = 8; 8 - 15 = -7; -7 + 12 = 5; 5 - 25 = -20; -20 - 22 = -42}{9}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{-42}{9} = -\\frac{14}{3} \\approx -4.6667\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Subtract the mean from each data point and square the result\n\n$$\n\\begin{align*}\n(-11 - (-\\frac{14}{3}))^2 &= \\left(-\\frac{23}{3}\\right)^2 = \\frac{529}{9} \\\\\n(9 - (-\\frac{14}{3}))^2 &= \\left(\\frac{43}{3}\\right)^2 = \\frac{1849}{9} \\\\\n(5 - (-\\frac{14}{3}))^2 &= \\left(\\frac{29}{3}\\right)^2 = \\frac{841}{9} \\\\\n(15 - (-\\frac{14}{3}))^2 &= \\left(\\frac{59}{3}\\right)^2 = \\frac{3481}{9} \\\\\n(-10 - (-\\frac{14}{3}))^2 &= \\left(-\\frac{16}{3}\\right)^2 = \\frac{256}{9} \\\\\n(-15 - (-\\frac{14}{3}))^2 &= \\left(-\\frac{31}{3}\\right)^2 = \\frac{961}{9}"
